Question: I understand you are familar with the Keto weight loss program. Can you tell me if you would recommend it?  And how does it differ from the orignal high protein, low carb diet of the past?
Answer:
I'm not taking any pills. I feel like most of that stuff is a scam or could actually be harmful in the end. (Niall tagged me in a keto pill post)
  
  It's probably the same? Just more macro based, maybe. Lots more information on it, apps like Carb Manager and such.
  
  We've only really found alternatives for flours, sugar, salt, and stuff like that. My sister did end up buying a ketone meal replacement but I haven't tried it yet.
  
  Just been eating keto foods, exercise. No pills besides my metformin (pcos) and a multivitamin when I feel like it. It's the one i usually take.. not anything new on keto lol
  
  15.5 down since Jan 9th
  
  I'm not sure that I'd recommend pills to anyone. But eating keto could help people. Everyone's journey is different. I've noticed some that dropped a ton in the first month. I'm going into my 3rd month soon and only 15.5 down on keto. There's also different types of keto too - strict, dirty and lazy. I'm losing more inches since I workout. Basically average a 2 pound loss each week...

  "Arizona Representative Heather Carter (R-Cave Creek) is pushing restrictions on access to vapor products in order to combat underage access and use.
  
  Carter’s proposed legislation, SB1009 would treat vapor products as tobacco products at the state level where age verification is concerned. It would also give the Arizona Attorney General’s office the task of conducting age verification compliance checks on retailers which sell vapor products, as it currently does with tobacco products.
  
  SB1009 is not alone on the docket, however. Arizona Senator John Kavanough (R-Fountain Hills) would impose restrictions statewide against vaping in public accommodations such as bars, restaurants, the common areas of hotels and of apartments, and more.
  
  Kavanaugh may have a tougher time implementing his proposed bill, HB 2024, because it is legally an amendment to Arizona’s existingSmoke Free Arizona Act, passed in 2006. An amendment to that legislation would require a Yes vote from three quarters of both Arizona’s House and Senate in order to pass."

Question: do you plan your meals? if so, do you use an app(s) to help or do you do it all by yourself? how do you combine healthy, money saving and variety? Tell me your secrets!
Answer:

  buy what you need. Just because something is on sale doesn't mean you need X amount of it especially when its something that you rarely have. be a bit picky
  
  most stores also price down meat if its going to expire real soon.
  
  I will be meal prepping sometime this week. I don't really plan my meals. I just go by feeling or I'll see something on instagram, keto fb group or pinterest and want to try it out. great recipes. Sometimes I'll look up IG hashtags for specific items and see the recipes/pictures and get ideas.
  
  I'm sure there are meal planning apps or websites out there. I don't use them. I was using myfitnesspal to track food but Carb Manager is way easier to use while on keto. CM does have recipes on it but you need to pay the premium & I'm not about that 😂
  
  like last night i had chicken and broccoli, ate half and still have some for today. easy hacks like that help.

Question: Is asking someone's parents for permission to propose to their child more respectful or disrespectful in your opinion?
Answer:
If you two never talked about marriage at all and they went behind your back to ask then i feel like that could be disrespectful. You should really talk about marriage with the person way before they ask you. Or you ask them!
  
  It's a nice gesture but obviously outdated at the same time. Either way, at the wedding they'd "give you away" so I just view it in that way? It's their blessing. I feel like if the parents and the soon-to-be bride/groom didn't get along at all then f8ck even asking to begin with lol. Hopefully both are adults and can make their own decisions on the best way to move forward. There's a lot of different wedding etiquette to be looked at.
  
  I think it would be a better surprise to tell parents you got engaged instead of all "we knew" kind of thing but I don't really see getting their blessing a bad thing either.
  
  Personally, I could careless what my dad had to offer up but knowing what my mom thought would be nice. Clearly, I'd know ahead of time on her views on the s/o.

Question: Insulin resistance. I'd that like diabetes?
Answer:
Difference between insulin resistance vs diabetes
  
  "There might be some similarities in the diagnosis of diabetes and insulin resistance, but they are different medical conditions. In case of IR, the beta cells will keep producing insulin. Even after the muscle and fat cells become resistant to insulin, the pancreas will keep producing more insulin to help the body cells absorb the glucose that has accumulated in the bloodstream. On the other hand, diabetes occurs when the pancreas fails to produce enough insulin or the body becomes resistant to insulin. However, in the long run, IR can lead to prediabetes, which, if not treated, can progress to diabetes. There is no evidence to show why some people develop insulin resistance while others develop a sensitivity to insulin."
